.TH POOLD 8 "2025" "POOL Protocol" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
poold \- POOL protocol daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B poold
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B poold
is the POOL protocol daemon. It loads the pool kernel module (if not already
loaded), starts a listener, and manages session lifecycle including automatic
rekeying and heartbeat monitoring.
.PP
.B poold
is typically started via systemd:
.RS
.B systemctl start poold
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-p \fIport\fR
Listen on the specified port (default: 9253).
.TP
.B \-d
Run in foreground (do not daemonize). Useful with systemd.
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose logging to stderr.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /dev/pool
POOL kernel module device.
.TP
.I /etc/pool/poold.conf
Optional configuration file.
.TP
.I /var/lib/pool/
State directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR poolctl (8),
.BR pool_bridge (8),
.BR pool_relay (8)
